subsection.p:
(76) 








a.
activities: express an ongoing action with no inherent end-point (examples are run, smoke a pipe, play the piano, push something);


b.
accomplishments: express an event with an internal time structure and an end-point (examples are paint a picture, make a chair, build a house);


c.
achievements: express instantaneous events (examples are recognize something, reach the summit, cross the border);


d.
states: do not express an event or activity (examples are have something, love somebody, know something).
